==English==
===Etymology===
Shortened from '''[[Pakistani]]'''

===Proper noun===
'''Paki''' (''plural'' '''Pakis''')

#(''derogatory, offensive and racist'') A [[Pakistani]], or, more generally, a person of who is perceived to be a Pakistani; often applied to persons of any South Asian or Middle Eastern origin.

===Proper adjective===
'''Paki''' (''no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')

#(''derogatory, offensive and racist'') [[Pakistani]], or perceived to be Pakistani.

====Usage notes====
'''Paki''' became offensive during the 1960s when used by British tabloids to refer to immigrants in a derogotary and racist manner. In recent times there has been a trend by second- and third-generation British Pakistanis to reclaim the word, such as in the name of the clothing comany PAK1 or the activist website [http://paki.tv paki.tv]

